  "time_ut": 1658996672,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Emergency law is against the policies of Potottuwa",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Its Founding President, Member of Parliament Professor G.L Peiris said that the imposition of Emergency Law is against the policies and constitution of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna.",
        "Mr. GL Peiris said that it may adversely affect Sri Lanka at the Human Rights Commission, which will be held in Geneva next month, and it may also lead to the loss of the GSP Plus concession.",
        "He said that according to the current situation in Sri Lanka, the existing general law is sufficient to protect people's lives and property, and there is no need to impose the emergency law.",
        "Professor GL Peiris said this while addressing a press conference held today (28) in Colombo."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "Potottuwa",
          "label": "PERSON"
        }
